{
  "texts": [
    "16 and 17, averaged from the reviewed literature that mentioned in Sect. 4, highlight that the type of SCM and its replacement ratio play a crucial role in determining both workability and setting time.",
    "Mechanical propertiesFigure 18 summarizes the average increases in compressive strength obtained by using different SCMs at various replacement ratios, drawing from the literature reviewed in this paper Sect. 4.",
    "Bentonite, at a 15% replacement level, achieves the highest increase in compressive strength, with an improvement of around 50%, which underscores its significant role in strengthening the mixture.",
    "EGP, also at a 15% replacement ratio, shows a similarly notable improvement, further confirming its effectiveness in enhancing compressive strength.",
    "In contrast, Zeolite and SCBA, both at the same 15% replacement level, demonstrate comparatively smaller gains, indicating their more limited impact in this context."
  ]
}